    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned something about an escrow account for the closing and i'm kinda confused. what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the house purchase?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow is a neutral third party that holds funds or documents in a transaction until certain conditions are met. In the context of a house purchase, it ensures that the funds for the down payment and other closing costs, as well as any remaining purchase price, are only released to the seller once all conditions of the sale are fulfilled, like repairs being completed and inspections passed. It adds security to the transaction and helps protect both buyer and seller.",
