      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, the money sits safely in the escrow account while the transaction process completes. The escrow service can be separate from your lawyer, though many real estate attorneys provide escrow services, too. Insurance companies and some banks also offer escrow services for house purchases. The account is typically monitored by a bank or an escrow firm, which will manage the funds on either party's behalf until the transaction conditions are met, at which point it gets released as agreed. This way, the money isn't just sitting around; it's being held responsibly and securely until it's time to be distributed.",
